Hi James,

Back when I still investigated haunted sites, our team did this =
on various occasions within a house where we recorded several hours of acti=
vity over a few years (a long term investigation). We would leave our audio=
 equipment recording in several &quot;hot spots&quot; all over the house and then lea=
ve for an hour or two. I have to say, in our experience we never got an EVP=
 while we were out of the house. As a matter of fact we had an EVP when we =
reentered the house saying, &quot;here they come, lets go&quot;. I don&#39;t necessarily =
understand why a ghost or spirit would talk with no one present to receive =
the message unless during setup you explained what you are trying to accomp=
lish and what the spirits roll is in the experiment (we never tried explain=
ing). A piece of machinery (recorders) in an empty room does not have a con=
sciousness or spiritual presence I would be interested to see if you get di=
fferent results.

Regards,

Frank

